AUDIO: 'of the state-of-the-art models, which are like tens of thousands of times larger. Here\'s another impressive thing. It\'s also able to solve mazes and sudoku puzzles which all of these state-of-the-art models could not solve.'

[39:26] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'They all got 0%. But you can see that this TRM model, which is only 7 million parameters, was able to solve most of these puzzles. Now, this is quite a technical paper, but I\'ll try to explain'

[39:38] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'how this works in really simple terms. Basically, instead of trying to solve a problem in one go, this TRM model solves it repeatedly by improving its answer step by step. It first starts with a'

[39:51] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'guess at the solution and then it goes through this tiny neural network to basically refine its answer many times, each time learning from its previous tries. So this is basically a recursive'

[40:03] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'process and the AI model improves its answer more and more as it loops through this architecture and eventually it\'s able to actually let the model think deeply and reason better without actually requiring a huge neural network'

[40:16] [scene:talk]
